# GitHub Pages & Static Hosting

## Hosting Model

- Static Vite build deployed to GitHub Pages
- Build output: `dist/` folder
- No server-side rendering, no custom backend

## Deployment Workflow

GitHub Actions workflow: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- Triggered on push to `main`/`master` or manual dispatch
- Steps: `npm ci` -> `npm run build` -> upload `dist/`

## Vite Configuration

- `base: '/trend-studio/'` for repo subpath
- `build.outDir = 'dist'`
- Build script copies `index.html` to `404.html` for SPA fallback

## Static Files

- `public/robots.txt` is copied to `dist/robots.txt`
- `public/sitemap.xml` is copied to `dist/sitemap.xml`

## SPA Routing

- Client-side routing with `react-router-dom` `BrowserRouter`
- `basename={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}` in BrowserRouter
- Deep link refresh works via `404.html` SPA fallback

## Local Testing

- Dev: `npm run dev`
- Production preview: `npm run build && npm run preview`
- Do NOT open `dist/index.html` via `file://`
